SHA-256 of text input up to 503 bytes (1 to 8 blocks).
Generalizes the 2-block version (PR #71) to arbitrary block count.
n_blocks formula extended to 8-way if/else: ceil((len + 9) / 64).
iterate_blocks recursion unchanged — only the static bounds widen.
Validated against sha256sum for inputs of every block boundary
(0, 55, 56, 119, 120, 183, 184, 503).
sha256_word entry rule, padded_byte/w_init_block helpers.
compress unchanged from PR #70.
